column5: Anyone going to Picton tomorrow? 8 of us leaving in the morning 5am for 3 days.
Have a good and safe time out there, Dave. Looks like rain for Tuesday and Wednesday but not cold.
Have fun Dave! Looks like a windy week with a few peeks of sunshine. Don't forget the Scotch...
Thanks Roy, Good time to try the new rain suit out.  Yes Wayne,you got that right. looks like I'll be fishing the calmer shore lines, I sold my bigger boat  , be using the smaller one.
send me a email will help you out
Thanks Lloyd, Email sent. May even see you tomorrow if your out.
Update?  Heading up next week for a day....
I fished Friday and got skunked and then Saturday got 2.  We were fishing from the Keiths to Prinyers on the south shore.  Our 2 fish came on firetiger up high in 90-100 fow.
Going up next weekend...keep the reports coming!
